Regresja liniowa¶

  • Analityczna regresja wykorzystuje wzr matematyczny szybka, ale wraliwa na problemy z macierz.
  • Numeryczna regresja opiera si na optymalizacji dziaa zawsze, ale moe by wolniejsza.

Regresja analityczna¶

y = ax + b

w[0] to wspczynnik kierunkowy a

w[1] to wyraz wolny b

Uywamy wzoru: w = (X X) X y

In [46]:
def analytical_linear_regression(X, y):
    Xt = X.T
    w = np.linalg.inv(X @ Xt) @ X @ y.T
    w = w.flatten()
    return w[0], w[1]

Regresja numeryczna¶

Zamiast oblicza wzr, szukamy minimum funkcji bdu (redni bd kwadratowy) iteracyjnie (np. scipy.optimize.minimize). Naley uywa gdy danych jest duo, s nieliniowe lub le uwarunkowane

Uywamy scipy.optimize.minimize, by znale najlepsze a i b.

In [47]:
def loss(w, X, y):
    w = w.reshape(-1, 1)
    predictions = X.T @ w
    return np.mean((y.T - predictions) ** 2)

def numerical_linear_regression(X, y):
    D = X.shape[0]
    w0 = np.zeros(D)
    result = minimize(loss, w0, args=(X, y), method='Powell')
    return result.x[0], result.x[1]

import time

iterations = 100

start_time_analytical = time.time()
for _ in range(iterations):
    analytical_linear_regression(X, y)
end_time_analytical = time.time()

start_time_numerical = time.time()
for _ in range(iterations):
    numerical_linear_regression(X, y)
end_time_numerical = time.time()

time_analytical = end_time_analytical - start_time_analytical
time_numerical = end_time_numerical - start_time_numerical

print(f"Czas wykonania analytical_linear_regression dla {iterations} iteracji: {time_analytical:.4f} sekund")
print(f"Czas wykonania numerical_linear_regression dla {iterations} iteracji: {time_numerical:.4f} sekund")

Zadanie na 4¶

Porwnanie sklearn i analitycznej implementacji regresji na zbiorze FlapPy Bird

Napisanie funkcji z wykorzystaniem PolynomialFeatures i LinearRegression¶

In [51]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

def polynomial_regression(x, y, degree):
    poly = PolynomialFeatures(degree=degree)
    X_poly = poly.fit_transform(x.reshape(-1, 1))
    
    model = LinearRegression()
    model.fit(X_poly, y)
    
    y_pred = model.predict(X_poly)
    
    mse = mean_squared_error(y, y_pred)
    
    return y_pred, mse

Wasny model regresji

In [52]:
def analytical_polynomial_regression(X, y, degree):
    if X.ndim == 1:
        X = X.reshape(-1, 1)
    
    X_poly = np.ones((X.shape[0], degree + 1))
    for d in range(1, degree + 1):
        X_poly[:, d] = X[:, 0] ** d
    
    Xt = X_poly.T
    w = np.linalg.inv(Xt @ X_poly) @ Xt @ y
    
    y_pred = X_poly @ w
    mse = np.mean((y - y_pred) ** 2)
    
    return y_pred, mse

def get_data(file_name):
    file_path = f'./datasets/flappy/{file_name}.csv'
    data = pd.read_csv(file_path, header=None, names=['x', 'y'])

    x = np.array(data['x'].values)
    y = np.array(data['y'].values)

    return x, y

x_all_points, y_all_points = get_data('all_points')

Normalizacja pobranych danych - do zakresu (0, 1)

In [54]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler

def minimize_data(x, y):
    scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(-1, 1))
    x_minimized = scaler.fit_transform(x.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()
    y_minimized = scaler.fit_transform(y.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()
    
    return x_minimized, y_minimized

x_all_minimized, y_all_minimized = minimize_data(x_all_points, y_all_points)
x_min_minimized, y_min_minimized = minimize_data(x_min_points, y_min_points)
x_changes_minimized, y_changes_minimized = minimize_data(x_only_changes, y_only_changes)

def plot_results(x, y, y_pred, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.scatter(x, y, label='Dane', color='blue')
    plt.plot(x, y_pred, label='Regresja', color='red')
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

Zadanie na 5¶

Analityczn wersja regresji z regularyzacj Tichonowa (ridge regression). Porwnanie dziaania wasnej implementacji z sklearn.linear_model.Ridge na zebranych zbiorach.

Własna implementacja regresji z regularyzacją Tichpova¶

In [59]:
def regression_with_Tichonov(x, y, alpha, degree):
    X = np.vstack([x**d for d in range(degree + 1)]).T
    Xt = X.T
    I = np.eye(X.shape[1])
    
    w = np.linalg.inv(Xt @ X + alpha * I) @ Xt @ y
    y_pred = X @ w
    
    mse = np.mean((y - y_pred) ** 2)
    
    return y_pred, mse

Regresja z wykorzystaniem model.Ridge¶

In [60]:
from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge

def regression_with_Tichonov_model_ridge(x, y, alpha, degree):
    poly = PolynomialFeatures(degree=degree)
    X_poly = poly.fit_transform(x.reshape(-1, 1))
    
    model = Ridge(alpha=alpha)
    model.fit(X_poly, y)
    
    y_pred = model.predict(X_poly)
    mse = mean_squared_error(y, y_pred)
    
    return y_pred, mse

In [63]:
def generate_comparison_plot(mse_results, datasets, degrees):
    labels = [name for name, _, _ in datasets]
    x_labels = [f"{name} (deg {degree})" for name in labels for degree in degrees]
    x = np.arange(len(x_labels))

    width = 0.35
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(x - width/2, mse_results["Sklearn"], width, label="Sklearn")
    plt.bar(x + width/2, mse_results["Analytical"], width, label="Analytical")
    plt.xlabel("Dataset and Degree")
    plt.ylabel("MSE")
    plt.title("Comparison of MSE for Sklearn and Analytical Tichonov Regression")
    plt.xticks(x, x_labels, rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

generate_comparison_plot(mse_results, datasets, [degree])

Wnioski¶

  • obie metody (wasna i z modelu) daj te same wyniki
  • alpha dzia tylko dla minimalnego zbioru (dla 0.1 all_points wynosio okoo 0.18 a dla 0.0001 wynioso 0.12, only_changes zostao prawie bez zmian a min_points dla 0.0001 wynioso okoo 0.11 a dla 0.1 wynioso okoo 0.27)
